transcripts.text: So when Dominion said they would come in and answer the question, this was an opportunity for them to demonstrate who they were, the services they were providing, the products that they were selling us, and how they were being utilized.  Unfortunately, their rescinding their acceptance of participation in our committee hearing robbed our voters of that information.

That was Pennsylvania State Representative Dawn Kiefer just moments ago slamming officials.  She was talking about Dominion voting systems after they backed out, as she said, of a hearing at the state capitol.  Newsmax White House correspondent Edward Robinson has been following these fast-moving developments.  From my knowledge, Emerald, this is the first time we've heard from Giuliani and friends, if you will, of the campaign.  We've heard from them about Dominion.  This is the first time I've seen a state actually come out about Dominion.  Tell me about this.
